 Write a python program to check whether the given three sides of a triangle are valid or not.

program:
 a = float(input("Enter the length of side a: "))
b = float(input("Enter the length of side b: "))
c = float(input("Enter the length of side c: "))
if (a + b > c) and (a + c > b) and (b + c > a):
    print("The sides can form a triangle.")
else:
    print("The sides cannot form a triangle.")

output:
 Enter the length of side a: 2
Enter the length of side b: 6
Enter the length of side c: 6
The sides can form a triangle.
